==Personal life==
Powell has two older sisters, Joniece and Margaret. He majored in History at [[University of California Los Angeles]].<ref name=ucla_bio/>

In October 2017, Powell teamed with web host [[GoDaddy]] to launch his website and his first [[single (music)|single]] "No Problem".<ref>{{cite news|last=Loung|first=Steven|title=Raptors’ Powell launches music website, releases song ‘No Problem’|date=October 30, 2017|website=Sportsnet.ca|url=http://www.sportsnet.ca/basketball/nba/raptors-powell-launches-music-website-releases-song-no-problem/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222105014/http://www.sportsnet.ca/basketball/nba/raptors-powell-launches-music-website-releases-song-no-problem/|archivedate=December 22, 2017|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/GoDaddy-Canada-and-Toronto-Raptor-Norman-Powell-team-up-to-inspire-Canadian-small-businesses-1006175633|title=GoDaddy Canada and Toronto Raptor Norman Powell team up to inspire Canadian small businesses|work=businessinsider.com|date=October 30, 2017|accessdate=December 23, 2017}}</ref>

